```text
IDE/project instruction -> escape-zombie-school Kanban board -> real Hermes profile worker -> project-local artifact
```

## Current Spawnable Profiles

Use these real Hermes profile names for durable Kanban cards:

- `threemini`: Three.js/R3F graphics, toon rendering, VFX, runtime visuals.
- `uimini`: UI/HUD/UX, responsive layout, touch targets, overlays, menus.
- `levelmini`: gameplay loop, stage flow, leveling, difficulty, weapon/card planning.
- `balanceqa`: QA gates, risk register, integration synthesis, browser/mobile validation.
- `bizmini`: product scope, business model, monetization tradeoffs.
- `launchmini`: Google Play, internal testing, policy, AAB/release readiness.
- `backendmini`: Firebase/backend boundaries, privacy, account deletion architecture.
- `englishgradmini`: English copy, store text, localization readiness.
- `madangsue`: operations ledger, environment hygiene, smoke-test support.
- `jabdareminder`: reminder and notification hygiene.

## Guardrails

- Follow `project_develop_policy.md` first.
- Role records must stay in their role folders: `Planner/`, `Developer/`, `Graphic_designer/`, `Quaility_Assurance/`, `CEO/`, or the relevant project-local folder.
- Preserve existing uncommitted user/agent changes.
- Do not commit, push, reset, delete, or submit to Google Play unless Terry explicitly asks.
- Worker output must include exact files read, files changed, commands/tests run, blockers, risks, and handoff notes.

## Acceptance Shape

Each specialist wave should produce:

- concrete project-local artifact,
- exact files inspected,
- exact files created or updated,
- commands/tests run,
- blockers and next recommended cards,
- cross-role handoff notes.

